FBIS4-17133 "drsov077_b_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin: Balance Between Powers `Taking Shape' Yeltsin: Balance Between Powers `Taking Shape' LD2004145394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1402 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004145394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] [Text] Moscow, 20 Apr -- "A balance between the executive and representative powers is taking shape." This was stated by Russian Federation President Boris Yeltsin at a meeting with the heads of administrations of Russian krays and oblasts, when he was summing up the results of elections to local bodies of power that had been held in a number of regions. According to Boris Yeltsin, "the elections were normal, though not everywhere was their quality good." In June there will be elections in the rest of the regions. "We must continue work to truly provide a real division of power," stressed Boris Yeltsin.
